{
  "stem": "19055.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 352.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And my sister fell in love with, with an American soldier, just as you see in the movies.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was a wonderful experience.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "One day, we heard more rumbling and more cannon fires.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the fear grabbed me again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we were terribly afraid of what's, what's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Maybe the Germans are coming back here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And an American GI was posted next to our house.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He were standing there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I still remember him with chewing gum and standing there with his gun.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I said to him-- because I knew a little English from my teacher, Schporer, the fencer-- Germans come back?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he looked at me, said, never, never.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "These were the English words I remember that they were told to me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I also remember an American doctor with his gold-rimmed glasses looking over me and listening to my chest in that field hospital.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And his name was Dr.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "White.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he pinched me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He says, no flesh, because there was no flesh.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was 30 kilograms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they treated us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They gave us clothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Americans put us together and then put big hoses in our clothing and sprayed us with DDT.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Everybody smelled DDT.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And finally, we got rid of, of our lice.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A small cemetery was started next to this Hillersleben where we were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sheltered.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this little cemetery was growing by the day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I would say half of our people who were there liberated died afterwards of typhus, of tuberculosis, or pneumonia, or I don't know what, or just weakness, or elementary problems.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "A few weeks later, I became yellow completely.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I acquired hepatitis in addition to my tuberculosis.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I'm still alive.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was no treatment for that, either.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's-- it was hepatitis.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "A, I think.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
